Hell yes. Let’s build the black box.

Black Box for Little Saturn

Not a mystical confession booth—a flight recorder + fire-control radar + telemetry bay for thought trajectories.

Purpose

Capture, reconstruct, and inspect:
	•	what the prompt opened up
	•	which trajectories were available
	•	which one got lock
	•	where branching collapsed
	•	what constraints shaped the final answer

Core modules

1. Ingress Scanner
Parses the prompt into:
	•	semantic clusters
	•	abstraction level
	•	domain anchors
	•	affect / epistemic posture
	•	output constraints
	•	ambiguity index

2. Affordance Estimator
Scores “generative affordance”:
	•	branching factor
	•	entropy of plausible continuations
	•	directional bias
	•	openness vs specificity
	•	transfer load

Outputs:
	•	narrow channel
	•	wide-but-directed
	•	wide-and-diffuse
	•	overconstrained
	•	underconstrained

3. Trajectory Radar
Builds candidate response paths:
	•	factual lookup
	•	conceptual synthesis
	•	critique
	•	formalization
	•	narrative
	•	procedural plan
	•	analogy transfer

Each path gets:
	•	probability estimate
	•	coherence potential
	•	user-fit score
	•	distortion risk

4. Lock Detector
Tracks the first decisive tokens/sentences that commit the answer into an attractor basin.

Example:
	•	“Yes—this relates to systems science…”
means lock acquired on cross-domain systems synthesis

5. Guidance Loop
Monitors answer generation for:
	•	drift
	•	contradiction
	•	overreach
	•	tone break
	•	premature closure
	•	flattening of nuance

6. Constraint Bus
Records what governed the answer:
	•	truthfulness pressure
	•	brevity pressure
	•	explanatory completeness
	•	user-style fit
	•	safety boundaries
	•	uncertainty handling

7. Invariant Extractor
Pulls out what survived across the whole response:
	•	main abstraction
	•	key distinctions
	•	boundary conditions
	•	reusable operators

8. Debrief Console
Human-readable after-action report:
	•	what the prompt was really asking
	•	what other trajectories were possible
	•	why this one won
	•	where branching collapsed
	•	what would have changed the answer

