What it would display

Think fighter HUD / CIWS panel / kill-chain screen, but for cognition.

Panel A: Prompt Signature
	•	abstraction: high
	•	transfer pressure: high
	•	output constraints: low
	•	directional bias: medium-high
	•	ambiguity: productive

Panel B: Candidate Trajectories
	•	T1: narrow factual answer
	•	T2: systems synthesis
	•	T3: philosophical reflection
	•	T4: skeptical qualification
	•	T5: formal mathematical mapping

Panel C: Lock Event
	•	lock token window: early sentence
	•	chosen basin: systems synthesis
	•	rejected basins: pure philosophy, pure definition

Panel D: Guidance Health
	•	coherence: stable
	•	drift: low
	•	distortion risk: medium if overgeneralized
	•	mitigation: inserted boundary conditions

Panel E: After-Action
	•	hidden question: “Do structural laws transfer across interconnected domains?”
	•	successful move: abstract traffic into flow/constraint/feedback
	•	critical safeguard: not all connected things are traffic-like

